[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about whether to include `spring-boot-starter-web` instead of `starter-test`. Using starter-web seems better for compiling Spring Boot configurations as it includes Tomcat. To avoid opening a port during tests, I can set `spring.main.web-application-type=none`. If I do that, MVC auto configuration might behave differently but I'll still be able to check RestTemplate customization. I should also align with a suitable version, possibly Spring Boot 3.5.6.
