se areas to make sure everything functions smoothly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"The artifact is a Spring Boot autoconfiguration module with Spring Boot and Spring Web classes as compile-only/optional usage; meaningful coverage requires a Spring Boot test/application classpath beyond the target artifact itself.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-web:3.5.16\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Provides the Spring Boot, Spring Web, Spring MVC, servlet, and logging classes needed to load and exercise the autoconfiguration entries exposed by the artifact.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-test:3.5.16\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Provides Spring Boot test utilities such as ApplicationContextRunner/Spring test support, matching how this autoconfiguration is normally verified without starting external services.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"When starting a Spring context, set test properties to avoid external telemetry export attempts, e.g. otel.traces.exporter=none, otel.metrics.exporter=none, and otel.logs.exporter=none. Prefer a small ApplicationContextRunner or non-network SpringApplication setup and close the context after assertions.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The module has optional autoconfigurations for Kafka, MongoDB, JDBC, R2DBC, WebFlux, Micrometer, and AOP; full feature coverage would require more libraries or services, but core/web autoconfiguration coverage is reachable without Docker.\",\n    \"Native Image and local Gradle verification remain authoritative for whether Spring Boot 3.5.x is acceptable in this repository's test harness.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d052127fe158bf6016a3e8d32ba308197ab283a33